text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild]]%0a%0a!Linguistic Discrimination during COVID-19 times%0a%0a:Author: BrandonW%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aSome examples of language discrimination due to COVID-19%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aA person's language or dialect is one of the ways that people are able to identify where a person comes from. But in COVID-19 times, people have discriminated others if they recognize that a person comes from areas that are considered hotspots for COVID-19.%0a%0aIn Hong Kong, most people speak Cantonese while the official language in China is Mandarin. So, Hong Kong residents have considered people who are known to speak Mandarin to be threats to their public health as China is one of the hotspots for COVID-19. Specifically, many Mandarin speakers have been refused service by more than 100 restaurants in Hong Kong.%0a%0aIn China, people listen for accents/dialects that distinctly come from Hubei Province, which is where COVID-19 outbreak started, and will shun these type of people. Examples include avoided these people on public transportation or denying them entry to public spaces or restaurants.%0a%0aIn Europe, Italy is one of the hotspots for the virus. Some Italians that have traveled abroad have been discriminated against for speaking their native language. An example is a man from Italy who traveled to Slovenia who got beat and robbed and called "Italiano coronoavirus" after people in Slovenia heard him speaking Italian.%0a%0aSource: https://undark.org/2020/05/05/covid-19-language-discrimination/%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a(:section: C:)%0a(:Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild:)
